  "text": "We also asked whether the loci that paired after b-estradiol induction were present preferentially on the nuclear periphery. This is of interest because of multiple known functional roles of localization to the nuclear periphery (Introduction); because the loci being tested were positioned near their respective telomeres, which can tend to be peripherally-associated [CITATION_1] ; and because, in particular, transcription-induced re-localization of galactose-inducible genes has been demonstrated in yeast [CITATION_2] .",
